<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-3658] NRTCachingDir has invalid asserts (if same file name is written twice)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-3658</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;Normally Lucene is write-once (except for segments.gen file, which NRTCachingDir never caches), but in some tests (TestDoc, TestCrash) we can write the same file more than once.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t think NRTCachingDir should have these asserts, and I think on createOutput it should remove any old file if present.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I also found &amp;amp; fixed a possible concurrency issue (if more than one thread syncs at the same time; IndexWriter doesn&apos;t ever do this today but it has in the past).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
